## Why CC BY-SA for Workbench Learnings

The lane documents, friction patterns, parked specs, and belief
archives represent thousands of hours of operational agent-system
design. They are the "source code" of the Workbench control plane's
thinking, not just reference docs.

Apache 2.0 would allow a company to:
1. Fork all learnings into a private repo
2. Add their proprietary improvements
3. Rebrand and sell without attribution or sharing back

CC BY-SA 4.0 prevents "embrace, extend, extinguish" while still
allowing commercial use. If Vercel builds on our lane docs to
improve their Open Agents platform, those improvements must also
be CC BY-SA. The upstream stays open, the chain of attribution
is unbroken, and Workbench remains the canonical source.
